Class Employee

java.lang.Object
Employee
public class Employee extends Object
Backend class for accessing and manipulating employee table values as well as creating and inserting new orders to both the order_info and order_items tables

    • createOrder

      public static void createOrder(double totalprice, String date, String time, Vector<Integer> itemids, Vector<String> sizes)
      Given the price of an order, current date, current time, item IDs and sizes of all the items in the order, adds a new entry into the order_info table as well as multiple entries into the order_items table corresponding to all items in the order
      Parameters:
      totalprice - Double value corresponding to the price of the newly created order
      date - Current date value (yyyy-mm-dd) of the newly created order
      time - String value of the current time correspoding to the newly created order
      itemids - Vector of integer values corresponding to all the itemids of the items in the newly created order
      sizes - Vector of string values corresponding to all the sizes of the items in in the newly created order
